From 60741745f6f70a2add683702f6471aaaf7172a5d Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: 10BE Software UG <support@ns.10be.de>
Date: Tue, 2 Jun 2026 11:07:09 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] Allow 10BE CarbCam to prefill the AddCarbs sheet

Adds a small URL-scheme entry point that lets 10BE CarbCam
(package de.be10.carbcam) hand its carb estimate over to Trio.
On URL receipt the AddCarbs sheet opens prefilled with the
supplied carb / fat / protein / notes values; the user must
still confirm via the standard Save and continue button before
anything is written to CoreData.

Design notes:

  * URL scheme: carbcam-trio://
  * URL format: carbcam-trio://carbs?value=N&fat=N&protein=N
                                    &notes=...&source=...
  * Validation: value 1..80 g (required), fat 0..80 g (optional),
    protein 0..80 g (optional), notes max 200 chars. Out-of-range
    values are silently rejected.
  * No caller identity check is performed: anyone can open the
    URL, but the user always confirms in the AddCarbs sheet
    before logging.
  * No silent CoreData writes, no silent bolusing. All existing
    confirmation flows are unchanged.
  * fat and protein are passed as separate URL parameters so
    Trio's existing UI fields can be prefilled directly without
    FPE-style 50/50 splitting heuristics.

Implementation:

  * TrioApp.handleURL gains a `carbs` host case and a small
    handleCarbCamURL helper.
  * A new ExternalCarbsPrefill enum acts as a one-shot prefill
    carrier (store / consume / hasValue). consume() clears the
    value as it returns, so a later manual re-open of AddCarbs
    does not re-apply the same prefill.
  * Home.StateModel listens for the .openAddCarbsFromCarbCam
    notification via Combine, toggling a new
    shouldDisplayCarbCamSheet @Observable property.
  * HomeRootView.body binds a new .sheet on the top-level ZStack
    (not on mainView) so the sheet appears regardless of which
    tab is active when the URL arrives.
  * Cold-start safe: ExternalCarbsPrefill.hasValue is checked at
    the end of HomeStateModel.subscribe(), so a URL that arrived
    before the listener was wired up still triggers the sheet on
    the next main-thread tick.
  * AddCarbsStateModel.subscribe() consumes the prefill at the
    end of its existing initialization, clamping each value
    against the corresponding max setting.

Target branch: Artificial-Pancreas/Trio main
